local policies for prevention and control of COVID-19 infection.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}},"1":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[{"length":4,"offset":0,"style":"bold"}],"key":"2l8os","text":"NOTE: Because ‘the edge’ of the water body may change due to precipitation changes, the edge should be defined at each month's sampling. If the water body has a "drop off" (embankment of more than 20cm), the soil and water samples should be taken where the water "meets" the soil. Aim to collect at locations where finer sediment is present, if possible.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}
